@lizthefeminist3 @StablersChain @WolfEnt @cvspharmacy @lawandordertv 100% would still love to have them talk about it, flash back to it, would love a whole hour that is JUST the Christmas party. lol But even a mention would do.

@StablersChain @lizthefeminist3 @WolfEnt @cvspharmacy @lawandordertv I think the writers rooms maybe don't communicate about little things. Like... BIG things yes, but I think when it comes to something like the Christmas party, which is big to us but not to the central plot of either show, I feel like things get dropped.

It sucks that we didn't get to see it. Truly, it does. I wish we had. But by all evidence, Olivia and Noah spent pre-Christmas Christmas with the Stablers, and I think we gotta stop letting anyone take that away from us. Even ourselves. Maybe especially ourselves. 

Own the win.

And if some anti tries to tell the EO fandom that it didn't?  Prove it.

Show me where it says Noah didn't decorate snowman sugar cookies with Kathleen. Show me where Bernie didn't slip Liv a hot toddy. Show me where Elliot didn't get TROUNCED in Mario Kart by the boys.

As far as what we got in canon, he invited, she accepted, and nothing has suggested she bailed on him. So I don't need more confirmation it DID happen, I say we take the win until we get confirmation it DIDN'T. They had nog and cocoa and made merry and it was a grand old time.

He asked, she said she'd think about it and let him know, and then we saw at the party that he fully expected Liv and Noah to be there when he opened the door to Bell. So clearly, she said she was coming. And since then, nothing has been said to indicate that she did NOT go.

Folks, I think we need to reframe how we look at this Christmas party. I think we've been pooping on our own party. We've spent months wanting someone to confirm it *did* happen, and I think we gotta start looking at this the *other* way.

Let me explain...
